==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[light]] [[rail]]}}

# {{US|transportation}} A kind of rail passenger transport with a dedicated [[right of way]], but crossing streets at [[grade]], usually for [[commuters]], powered by electricity, and with lower construction costs than traditional railroads.
#: ''The new Denver '''light rail''' runs along the Interstate highway.''

====Usage notes====
*[[streetcars|Streetcars]] (or [[trolleys]]) did not have their own rights of way. Traditional railroad commuter lines would have high construction costs. [[interurban|Interurban]] electic railroads were not much used for commuter service. [[subway|Subways]] and other [[rapid transit]], with few or no [[grade crossings]], also have high construction costs.

